                            <comment id="16445866" author="dsmiley" created="Fri, 20 Apr 2018 15:09:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So this method, EmbeddedSolrServer.request(...) confusingly looks up the requestHandler twice &#8211; once on the coreContainer reference (I wish there was a comment explaining why), and failing that then more normally further below at line 190:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/client/solrj/embedded/EmbeddedSolrServer.java#L190&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/client/solrj/embedded/EmbeddedSolrServer.java#L190&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You changed the first occurrence but not the second. Again; a test would have revealed this oversight I think. &#160;I&apos;ll cook up a patch. &#160;Maybe that would even happen indirectly if the SolrTextTagger were to be incorporated directly into Solr; a few&#160;people have asked me about this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
